HEADWORD: London smoke
<hw>Lon"don smoke</hw>. <def>A neutral tint given to spectacles, shade
glasses for optical instruments, etc., which reduces the intensity
without materially changing the color of the transmitted
light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

